To start the NetCat listening server, type
	sudo nc -l [ip] -p [port]
	ip will usually be localhost, port will usually be 80

Then, to send something, type
	echo [message] | nc [ip] [port]

It's really cool!
This was found on:
https://www.reddit.com/r/SolusProject/comments/6eh3vu/cant_get_netcat_to_work_with_sudo_nc_l_80/?st=j3elzt7c&sh=52d1cd43
